Should this be an `#adaptation_note`? Should there be a date string added?
```suggestion
        #adaptation_note
        /-- this used to be aesop_cat, but that broke with
        https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/pull/4154 -/
```

Is this related to the membership mem swap that is now fixed again? So this will be very transient?
If not, shall we add a date string?

```suggestion
    #adaptation_note
    /--
```
Or should we use some other marker, so that it will be recorded as tech debt?
We can't used adaptation note in term mode.
@jcommelin, we can't use #adaptation note in term mode.
